L’uomo sul treno di Jaume Collet-Serra Un film d’azione, per certi versi classico, le cui caratteristiche rientrano pienamente nel filone di film d’azione. Il protagonista è il solito uomo, arrivato per certi versi al limite (con l’età e le sue vicissitudini private), dalla moralità inflessibile e con capacità fuori dal normale, che si ritrova a dover salvare le vite dei passeggeri di un treno. Per certi versi dunque è un film classico senza grosse sorprese, qualche caratteristica leggermente curiosa, però, la troviamo: una fotografia ben curata con inquadrature di primi piani e di particolari molto ben fatte e la presenza di una regia che prova tramite qualche trucchetto e stratagemma a farsi un po’ furba. Lo sviluppo della trama è molto ordinato e procede in modo lineare e semplice per gran parte del film , così come il treno in questione, fino a poco prima del finale dove sia il racconto, che il treno, escono un po’ dai binari per un finale abbastanza originale. Una nota negativa personalmente l’ho trovata nelle scene d’azione, in cui si nota che Liam Neeson non è più un giovanotto e sente il bisogno di usare la CGI per certi combattimenti, cosa che rende le scene meno scorrevoli e fluide. In conclusione quindi un film d’azione carino che riesce a intrattenere senza alcun problema. The Commuter (2018) - 6/10 I really enjoyed this movie. Yeah its a over the top action movie but look this is what i want in a Liam Neeson action movie. It is like alot of Neeson’s other movies but its a movie you can just sit and enjoy and leave your worries behind. So you guessed this movie takes place on a train and with that you have a unique root you can take with the plot. Not quite sure why i enjoy movies that take place on a train ? Like i loved Murder on the Orient Express and then i really enjoyed this. The fighting scenes in this were surprisingly well editing and choreographed. Neeson can kick ass as usual. I like that Liam Neeson is trying to recreate a famous 80s movie ... first we had him in a Plane in Non-Stop, then we see him in this movie on a Train so I’m guessing we are going to see him in a movie where its set in a car. If you don’t get what I’m saying is the Liam Neeson is recreating Planes, Trains and Auto-mobiles. Overall its a really fun action flick that you don’t need to take seriously but its fun to watch. It stars Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson, Jonathan Banks, Elizabeth McGovern and Sam Neill. Its about insurance salesman Michael who is on his daily commute home, which quickly becomes anything but routine. After being contacted by a mysterious stranger, Michael is forced to uncover the identity of a hidden passenger on the train before the last stop. As he works against the clock to solve the puzzle, he realizes a deadly plan is unfolding, and he is unwittingly caught up in a criminal conspiracy that carries life and death stakes for everyone on the train. #thecommuter #movie #cinema #moviereview #moviemadness6

My first review! 'The Commuter' was the first movie I saw in 2018, and I'll therefore review it first. The premise of the movie, despite being a concurring premise, is pretty interesting. The plot is pretty good and driven by Michael's (Liam Neeson) love for his family. What I don't like about the story is that the movie ends, and there is still some mystery and unanswered questions. Vera Farmiga's character feels purposeless at the end of the movie and questions surrounding her remain untouched, which leaves her being a weak character. The action is fine for the most part but sometimes the way it's shot feels too extra in such a narrow area which is a train. In fact, the best parts are when Michael investigates subtly, rather than when he engages in action. During his investigations, the main character makes some rather questionable decisions that make you wonder where exactly he's trying to reach. The performances are good, and Liam Neeson stands out as usual. Overall, The Commuter is an enjoyable movie but feels like there's a bit more left to see by the end. Finalmente, sono riuscita a vedere L'uomo sul treno e mi è piaciuto moltissimo! Genere thriller, con un Liam Neeson un pò meno giovane, ma intenso e carismatico anche nei panni di un prevedibile assicuratore, che fa il pendolare 96. La trama del film è incentrata su lui e sul treno, ovviamente. Il titolo originale è "The Commuter", il pendolare, probabilmente chi ha tradotto il titolo, lo ha trovato un pò troppo minimalista e ha preferito "L'uomo sul treno", che a me non piace; considerando, che abbiamo appena visto "La ragazza del treno". Comunque il film non ha nulla in comune con quest'ultimo. Michael McCauley, ovvero Liam Neeson, viene improvvisamente licenziato dalla compagnia di assicurazioni per la quale lavora da oltre dieci anni. Si sfoga al bar con un suo ex collega poliziotto e amico, Alex Murphy, con cui è stato in pattuglia per oltre sette anni. Poi, riprende, tristemente, la via del ritorno. La perdita del lavoro non era prevista, due mutui, un figlio da mandare al college e la loro situazione bancaria non rosea. Michael non riesce ad immaginare nessun modo per comunicarlo alla moglie e al figlio. Sul solito treno, più affollato di quelli italiani, i soliti visi, più qualcuno nuovo, tra cui una donna, Joanna, che si siede proprio di fronte a lui e incomincia a parlare: "Che tipo di persona è lei? Se io le chiedessi di fare una cosa piccola, la farebbe?" The Commuter “Next time, I’ll take the bus.” Juame Collet-Serra Every Liam Neeson film that is released, is bound to be a solid thriller. Nothing fancy, but entertaining, no matter what situation, you’ll root for Liam Neeson because of his skills. Also, because he’s a great actor, doing all with what he has to work with. From saving his family multiple times, to dealing with scenarios of life and death in puzzling fashion, on a plane and now on a train, it pretty much ends the same predictable way. The Commuter keeps you interested, you can guess the villain in less than five minutes of this film, but you’ll like to see it unfold. It’s Murder on the Orient Express in present time sort of. Worth a matinee or rental, hopes shouldn’t be high but it’s likable, just don’t expect much but a time killer. Clean sequences, ok cast, cheesy script, and Liam Neeson, that’s all anyone ever needs sometimes. #thecommuter #liamneeson #patrickwilson #verafarmiga #samneill #film #filmaddict #movie #movieaddict #thursday #particularsetofskills #juamecolletserra #thriller

We watched The Commuter in the #movietheater. There are a lot of people comparing this to Nonstop. I can see why, both are thrillers on forms of transportation starring #LiamNeeson, but #thecommuter has a better script and makes for a more enjoyable #movie. Neeson plays Michael, an ex cop that has been working as an insurance salesman for the last ten years. He rides the commuter train into #NewYork each day, but then he gets laid off. He gets some drinks with his old partner Alex Murphy (not Robocop 98) played by #PatrickWilson. We also meet the police chief (#SamNeill), who Michael is surprised has risen that far. On his way home, a mysterious woman approaches him (#VeraFarmiga) and offers him $100K to find a person on the train. He’s desperate for money after losing his job and decides to play along. Little does he know what will happen once he finds the person. He begins to get an idea when he tries to call for help. People are killed and his family is in danger. It’s a good #thriller with some #mystery elements. The villains are very Machiavellian, but a huge corruption conspiracy is hinted and I like that we are kept mostly in the dark about it. It allows the villains motive to remain unknown. I also like that the #film subverts expectations on certain characters. It was solid and entertaining. 8215821582158215

Luego de realizar películas como “Non-stop” o “Desconocido”, Jaume Collet-Serra (director) y Liam Neeson (protagonista) se juntaron nuevamente para realizar otro thriller de acción. Y la fórmula sigue siendo más q satisfactoria. El film es muy ágil, atrapante y utiliza a la perfección la (prácticamente) única locación donde se desarrolla, un tren. Con escenas de acción en espacios reducidos, lo que favorece mucho a Neeson, y un guión que pese a algunos baches tiene buenos giros y sorpresas, “The commuter” consigue mantener al espectador enganchado hasta el final. Quizás la única mancha importante son algunas escenas exageradas e innecesarias sobre el final. Pero nada que una película de este género no pueda perdonar. Está claro que no hay novedad en la cinta. El tándem Collet-Serra/Neeson apela a una marca registrada en esta película. Pero haciendo esto no decepcionan. Al contrario, cumplen a la perfección la tarea de entretener. #4criticos #cine #cinema #peliculas #liamneeson #jaumecolletserra #thecommuter #elpasajero

"THE COMMUTER." (Still Showing on Bioskop . Cerita yang ditawarkan The Commuter relatif sederhana, hampir sama dengan film-film Liam Neeson sebelumnya seperti Taken dan Non-Stop ― Liam Neeson diminta menyelesaikan sebuah tugas demi menyelamatkan keluarganya. . Meskipun premis cerita yang ditawarkan cenderung membosankan, tapi tidak membuat film ini kehilangan keistimewaannya. Penonton dibuat seolah-olah ikut berada di dalam kereta, merasakan ancaman yang ada. Apa lagi bagi para anker (anak kereta) yang sehari-harinya menggunakan kereta commuter line untuk beraktivitas. . Adegan action di dalam kereta juga cukup membuat jantung terpacu saat menonton film ini. The Commuter (2018) Movie Review! 04 ________________________ Directed by: Jaume Collet-Serra ________________________ Plot: A businessman on his daily commute home gets unwittingly caught up in a criminal conspiracy that threatens not only his life but the lives of those around him. ________________________ Review: The first movie released in 2018 reviewed!!! The Commuter is another paired effort between Liam Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra. I really liked their airplane movie “Non-Stop”, and The Commuter is almost the same plot but on a train and Neeson’s character is more vulnerable. Let’s start with the positives. Liam Neeson is great once again here, chipping in a splendid performance and doing well in the action sequences. He may be getting old, but he can still pack many punches. The action is filmed quite nicely, not a lot of shaky cam and relying more on the emotional weight. You feel the punches and kicks thrown onboard the train. I also liked the sense of less atmosphere on the train, since it is an enclosed location. The camerawork and cinematography are great. Coming to the performances, I felt everyone else did serviceable. Patrick Wilson was fine, Vera Farmiga seemed wasted and a little off-key with her boring character, and Sam Neill was decent as the lead officer. Of course Neeson is worth making this movie enjoyable. The movie knows what it is, a simple thriller with a somewhat convoluted plot sadly. It’s never fully explained why Liam Nelson’s character is brought onto this mission. Into the negatives. There’s some really bad CGI in the nighttime sequences when the train crashes. The third act suffers with predictability to the villain, and the slow pacing can be felt. Overall, I felt The Commuter was a fine action movie, light on character development and stronger on entertainment value. ________________________ Verdict: 821582158215 #thecommuter #liamneeson #moviereview #movie #filmreview #film #theconjuring

My review of “The Commuter”- Going into this movie, my expectations weren’t too high. Working at my job for several hours prior, I was psychically and mentally exhausted, and I simply wanted to watch a fun movie that wouldn’t require me to use my brain too hard. With this in mind, “The Commuter” is exactly the kind of movie I wanted it to be, for better and (occasionally) for worse. Featuring frequent collaborators Liam Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra, this action flick is about a man named Michael who gets caught up in a criminal conspiracy while on a train after accepting a job that is given to him by a fellow passenger. Michael (played by Liam Neeson) is a pretty normal and unremarkable guy, with the films great opening segment showing just how repetitive (yet still enjoyable) his life his. Unfortunately, his life comes crashing down once he is inexplicably fired from his job, and he heads back home, sad and ashamed, on the train he has been on almost every day for the past ten years. Joanna (played by Vera Farmiga) is aware of Michael’s familiarity with the train and his recent firing, and uses these facts to give Michael an offer he can’t resist; for 100,000 dollars, he has too simply find someone on the train whom he feels doesn't belong. As Michael accepts the task, the movie kicks into gear. For a significant chunk of the movie, the pacing is swift and snappy, and I was captivated by the chaos that was taking place. Liam Neeson is to be thanked for my captivation, for he helps make Michael a very relatable and sympathetic character, which in turn makes one heavily invested in the fire journey he takes. Thankfully, this journey is well directed by Jaume Collet-Serra, who makes the action sequences very fun to look at and successfully allows the tension to pile onto itself. One fight in particular (involving an ax) had me on the edge of my seat as the fight neared its intense conclusion. Unfortunately, while this particular fight scene has a satisfying conclusion, the same can’t be said for the movie as a whole. (Continued in the comments section)

THE COMMUTER HE SAID: Have you seen the film Non Stop in which Liam Neeson plays a grizzled, Irish American lawman who receives a mysterious phone call and is challenged to find a mysterious passenger to prevent everyone from dying on the flight he is on? Yeah I’ve seen it too and I just rewatched the exact same film only this time it’s on a train and it’s called The Commuter! And here’s the thing - I enjoyed it...again! Taken was terrible (I didn’t bother watching 2 & 3) but it gave Neeson a new lease of life as an ageing action star and for the most part, his B-movie action films with this director have all been surprisingly enjoyable. This film also includes the best fight on a train since Sean Connery and Robert Shaw in From Russia With Love. One thing that’s really lacking in today’s cinematic climate is the mid budget action/thrillers of the 80’s and 90’s - where are your buddy cop movies? Your psychosexual drama? Your John Grisham adaptations? Your ticking clock suspense movies? Of late this is about as close as we’ve gotten to a straight up, fun B-movie and I’ll take(n) it. Instantly forgettable but fun all the same. SHE SAID: Imagine playing Cluedo with Agatha Christie on a train and Liam Neeson is your board piece: that’s The Commuter! The film opens with a sleek montage of mornings, giving depth to Neeson’s cop-turned-insurance broker backstory. His life immediately feels real, and we are ready to believe that he could and would wind up in one hell of an afternoon commute. Neeson is often an oxymoron: strong in stature but soft in manner. Here is a prime example, as he tries to locate a mysterious passenger while being framed as a hijacker who has seen Falling Down one too many times. We believe that he could beat a man using an electric guitar and that he could look like a nice guy while doing it. The Commuter is, to be fair, Non-stop on train tracks. And I’m ok with that. Next up, I hope Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra do a murder mystery on a cruise ship. They could call it Taken on Board!

"Todo comienza como cualquier trama de intriga, en la que sabes que las cosas no van a salir bien para nuestro desgraciado protagonista, y a medida que van pasando los minutos, esa intriga va cogiendo forma en tu estómago y en tu cabeza, creándose unas ilusiones, que van perdiendo un poco de fuelle, para aquellos impacientes adictos al caos y la acción empedernida, que no pueden pasar ni unos fugaces y necesarios “tranquilos” minutos, contemplando como lo mejor, está por llegar. Y llega cuando menos te lo esperas. Te pega un bofetada en la cara sin darte cuenta, dejándote sin respiración y las pulsaciones a mil, mientras contemplas escenas de infarto, en las que te tienes que agarrar a ti mismo o al desconocido del asiento del al lado, por miedo a salir disparado contra la butaca de atrás, si te alcanza alguna patada o bala perdida, en una trama que se mantiene intacta y sosegada, hasta que aumenta y estalla en mil pedazos, de brillante, y pura maestría cinematográfica. Jaume Collet-Serra, es un director, que sabe hacer películas, para toda clase de público, que lo que desea de verdad, es pasarlo verdaderamente mal, dejando de lado el género del drama, que ya se está repitiendo demasiadas veces, y que parece ser el único merecedor, de una inútil y clasicista estatuilla de oro. Jame Collet-Serra nos deja ver una vez más, que los espacios reducidos como un avión o un tren, son el escenario perfecto para desarrollar una trama explosiva, embaucadora y sobresaliente, que no deja a ningún espectador insatisfecho. Al contrario, nos sorprende, nos intriga, nos enga09a, nos manipula, y sobretodo, nos hace saltar por los aires, sin dejarnos un solo segundo para poder tomar aire, pensar en lo que está ocurriendo y en lo que puede ocurrir, y darnos la mínima oportunidad para acomodarnos y poder detener ese tic nervioso que hace acelerar aún mas, nuestra tensión, que se va esparciendo por todos los capilares de nuestra piel." The Commuter ~ PG-13 ~ 2018 ~ #JaumeColletSerra #LiamNeeson #VeraFarmiga #PatrickWilson #JonathanBanks #SamNeill #ColinMcFarlane After being laid off, a financially struggling businessman is offered the opportunity to find a specific person that doesn’t belong on his daily commuter train for a large amount of money. Okay, so I actually enjoyed this movie a lot more than I thought I would. Liam Neeson has had this stereotype ever since Taken where he plays yet another badass old guy in a mediocre, forgettable action movie. While The Commuter might still fall under that category, it definitely exceeded my expectations. Don’t get me wrong, there still are a fair amount of notable flaws. Character development was kept to a minimum, the acting was all relatively poor, & the third act is littered with an absurd amount of illogical writing. Regardless, this movie did what it’s main goal was: to entertain. As little invested as I was in the characters, the story remains consistent & fails to have a dull moment. The movie never takes itself too seriously, so I never really felt like the film was failing to do what it was trying to. I enjoyed the multiple scenarios Neeson’s character put himself in & even when the third act got a little over-the-top, I was still having fun. Would I ever watch this again on my own? Probably not. But I definitely didn’t find it to be the slightest of chores to watch this cheap thriller. 3/5 #TheCommuter #train #passenger #passengertrain #commuter #action #mystery #thriller #movie #film #moviereview

The Commuter is a movie starring Liam Neeson and directed by Jaume Collet-Sierra. The movie is about a man who is tasked by a woman to find a person with a certain bag going to a certain place and kill them. The movie is solid for the first two acts. It’s a nice action thriller with a race against the clock twist in an enclosed environment. It’s a fun movie, but with some odd “screw the upper-class” sentiments thrown in, but still solid. It brings good performances, and surprisingly good, but gimmicky direction. The third act, however goes completely off the rails, pardon my pun. It shifts the movie’s focus away from the interesting half mystery half action movie I was expecting, to a very overblown CGI mess. Without giving anything away, it almost shifts types of action movies to a completely different sub genre, and does some things that make no rational sense and may not even be possible. Another issue I have, is with the dialogue. It’s all very hokey and unrealistic. The attempts at comedy fall flat and the attempt at relating to the audience fails. All in all, it’s a perfectly passable movie, that is only accentuated by Jaume Collet-Sierra’s direction. #film #moviereview #movie #review #cinema #liamneeson #action #thriller #mystery #actionmovie #thecommuter #train

[Movie Review] The Commuter (2018) #KataKinema . The Commuter stars Liam Neeson as Michael McCauley, an ex-insurance salesman who is confronted by a mysterious woman, named Joanna (Vera Farmiga), on his daily commute home. Little did he know that Joanna is bad news, now Michael is blackmailed into finding someone on the train, where not only the lives of his family are at stake, but also the lives of everyone on the train. . I like the action scenes, I think they are well shot and well choreographed. I also like the thrilling whodunit moments. What I dislike, however, is the movie is taking itself too seriously, while there a lot of implausibilities and a few plot holes. If it doesn’t take itself seriously, I think I might’ve ignored the flaws and enjoyed it a little more. In conclusion, this movie is an enjoyable and thrilling action movie, only when you don’t try to make sense out of it. But if you do, it turns into an enjoyable, mindless, silly, and thrilling action movie. . KinemaScore: 2.5 out of 5 . So, what do you guys think? Let us know in the comment section! . Happy watching and we’ll see you at the movies :D . [疾速救援the commuter]推理惊悚片是我喜欢的电影类型之一，通常在选择看不看一部电影时，我会先看这部电影的导演和主角是谁，最后才是预告来决定看或不看。 导演Jaume Collet-Serra和主角Liam Neeson他们在这部电影已经是第四次合作了，而这部电影有点像他们之前合作的电影non-stop的剧情套路，都是在不知缘故的情况底下卷入一场危机中。 整部电影除了开头的镜头切换有点混乱外，其它的都在水准之中，虽然没有什么惊喜，但还算是一部精彩好看的电影。 故事从主角失业后，搭上一班他每天上下班都会搭的列车，而遇到一名神秘女子。她告诉主角，如果他可以帮助她完成一件小事就可以得到十万元的奖金。 这件小事就是要主角在这列车上找一个人，线索只有三个: 1.这个人的名字是普林，可能是假名。 2.拿着一个包，包里有一样不属于他的东西。 3.必须在他下车前找到他，他的终点站是冷泉站。 #疾速救援 #thecommuter

Movies of the Future: Weekend Box-Office Results 1: Maze Runner ($24.1M) 2: Jumanji ($16.1M) 3: Hostiles ($10.1M) 4: Greatest Showman ($9.5M) 5: The Post ($9.1M) Last weekend Maze Runner: The Death Cure was the major new release and it disappointed. However with its overseas numbers, it's already over $100M worldwide, but probably won't beat The Scorch Trials total of $312M worldwide. Jumanji just cant slow down with an amazing 17% drop as it'll soon race past $850M worldwide. Hostiles had a decent theatre expansion with a $10M haul. The Greatest Showman continues to boast incredible holds, but it'll just fall short of $300M worldwide. The Post is also doing god business, compared to 12 strong and Den of Thieves which has significantly slowed down. The Shape Of Water expanded further and got some good results but $50M worldwide isn't that great.

For Darkest Hour, I wrote a whole critic on my blog (link on bio) and I want an Oscar for Gary Oldman! Then, The Post really got me by portraying admirable determined journalists. Then, huge coup de c04ur on The Greatest Showman, been listening to the OST for a few days and I love Hugh Jackman singing and dancing. Then, Molly's Game was fine, interested characters and interaction between Chastain and Elba, but I wasn't that thrilled. Please, someone tell Liam Neeson to stop doing the same movies over and over again, The Commuter (The Passenger in Fr) was barely fine. Downsizing was pretty disappointing, just watch the trailer, all the interesting question are on it. Don't watch Fireworks, that Jap animated movie was way too much trying to be a new Your Name but meh you can't. And yeah I rewatched La La Land. THE COMMUTER CINERATE: 7 out of 10 CINEOPSYS Michael menghabiskan hari-harinya hidupnya di kereta utk perjalanan dr rmh ke tempat kerja. Hingga suatu hari, kedekatan hidupnya dengan dunia kereta sangat diperlukan utk memecahkan misteri yang membuat Michael, secara tidak langsung, terjebak dalam sebuah konspirasi kejahatan. CINENOTES Film ini sangat menonjolkan Liam Neeson sebagai tokoh protagonis. Sempitnya ruang geral di dalam kereta membuat semua aksi Liam Neeson terlihat maksimal. Untungnya, Liam memberikan performa terbaiknya untuk film ini. Awal film ini sangat artistik, sinematografi yang memukau terasa kira-kira sampai 20-25 menit pertama, selebihnya tidak ada efek visual yang sedinamis awalnya. Film ini memiliki logika filmnya sendiri, terutama bila mau mengupas logiks konspirasinya, sehingga cukup ditonton dengan menikmati setiap adegannya. Ada banyak kritik di dalamnya bila mau berpikir lebih keras, tapi sebuah pesan yang normatif. Kesimpulannya, film ini adalah sebuah cerita yang sederhana, dikemas dengan konspirasi yang pelik. THE COMMUTER: Director Jaume Collet-Serra specializes in entertaining junk, particularly entertaining junk starring Liam Neeson. These are the sorts of movies you enjoy while watching them, then forget about them almost immediately. This entry starts cleverly, gets particularly ridiculous with a very heavy, “yeah, right” quotient, then redeems itself with a finale so brazenly silly, I gave it points for chutzpah. For better entertaining junk by this director and star, see Unstoppable. For the best entertaining junk with this director, see The Shallows with Blake Lively. #thecommuter #liamneeson #sircritic

. THE COMMUTER . Michael MacCauley (Liam Neeson) ist Versicherungsmakler und führt ein beschauliches Leben. Seit zehn Jahren pendelt er jeden Tag mit dem Zug aus dem verschlafenen Vorort, in dem er mit seiner Familie lebt, nach Manhattan. Doch eines Tages wird seine Routine gest02rt: Er trifft w01hrend der morgendlichen Zugfahrt auf eine mysteri02se Fremde namens Joanna (Vera Farmiga), die sich zu ihm setzt und ihn in ein Gespr01ch verwickelt. Nach und nach offenbart sie Michael, dass sie nicht einfach nur an Smalltalk interessiert ist. Wenn er mit Hilfe von zwei vagen Hinweisen einen bestimmten Passagier an Bord des Zuges findet, dann winkt ihm eine hohe Belohnung. Sollte er sich jedoch weigern, ist nicht nur das Leben aller Mitreisenden in Gefahr, sondern auch das von Michaels Familie. Judul : the commuter Tahun : 2018 So, this movie mirip2 sama The Murder On The Orient Express. Pemecahan misteri di dalam kereta gt. Cuma ya beda background ceritanya aja, klo film ini si tokoh utama mantan polisi yang sekarang jadi agen asuransi #nahloh. Dia kaya dijebak gt sampe mau gak mau harus mecahin misteri untuk nemuin orang didalam kereta. Bingung juga ngereviewnya gmn, karena yaaaaaa kalau gw kasih tau udh ketauan dong semua misteri nya yah. Hahaha Ya the point is, kita akan diajak turut bersama dia memecahkan misteri yang harus dia pecahkan sebelum pemberhentian kereta terakhir. Film ini punya misteri dan kesimpulan yang bagus dan sepanjang film juga di bumbui sedikit action. But eiiiiits, bukan sampai disitu aja, setelah misteri terpecahkan masih ada yang harus diselesaikan sampai habis. Akhir film ini sih bagus yah, gak ganjtung gt. Lumayan bikin gregetan dan nahan napas sih sepanjang film. Overall yap okelah yah mayan, greget greget ngeselin gimanaaaa gituuu. Eniwey, so sorry sempat lamaaaaa kaga absen muka di bioskop karena kmrn holidey dulu biar kaya orang-orang. #kukamovietime #moviereview #reviewfilm #thecommuter #thecommutermovie #filmmisteri #detektif #cinemaxxi #cinemaxxisummareconserpong

The Commuter Directed by: Jaume Collet-Serra Starring: Liam Neeson, Patrick Wilson, Vera Farmiga A man on his daily commute back home is approached by a stranger with a hypothetical preposition, and a reward that is not so hypothetical. The first thing of notice that makes this a clever and engaging ride is the editing and camerawork; films primarily set in one location can easily become repetitive and lack the ability to make the audience anticipate what will happen next. Here however the editing creates a quickened pace that moves the plot along and makes this film feel like its supposed to (a thriller). It also manages to convey visual story-telling in a way that is so effective it removes the need for exposition. The camerawork keeps the location from ever feeling too familiar, the varying use of close-ups and tracking wide shots are relevant to the mood of the protagonist; and this causes his motivations and inner conflicts to be easily displayed on-screen. Not that that would be an issue anyway, as Liam Neeson proves again that he is the best at playing an "everyday-man" who knows how to kick ass. The film has a strong cast, although most of the other actors and actresses feel like they are only in cameo roles next to Neeson, who to allow the narrative to work well, is mostly isolated for the majority of the film. The tension is well built and it comes from being able to easily draw empathy from Neeson's performance; that is his best since Taken. The narrative proceeds logically although it bares a lot of noticeable similarities to other films (many of which I can't mention because...spoilers) but despite this it manages to be better than the films it either draws inspiration from or is coincidentally parallel to. The only negative to be seen is the fact that Neeson's character appears to have John McClane syndrome, and can be put through a lot more physical trauma than what you would expect of a man of his age, it doesn't detract from the fun of watching Neeson in action again but it is rather prevalent, and does have an impact on the validity of the character. Overall, a fast and cleverly put-together train ride that gives plenty to think about. 9/10

Next on the Liam Neeson's Transportation Conspiracy! THE COMMUTER Commuting isn't the most fertile source for interest when it comes to a movie, it's about a boring routine that you passionlessly do to get from point A to B. This film emulates all the thrills of commuting and resolves to meld them to an unnecessarily complicated plot. And, you know, it can be nice to take the train for the first time but once you've done it several times, it stops being refreshing. As so, if you see the same movie played out with slight differences over the course of a year, you lack that feeling of renewal - that's why John Wick's film are so appreciated, they bring something new. After having seen Non Stop and Run All Night, you can't help to be indifferent to the same actor-director combination, specially when the cuts, characters and plot feel the same, Jaume Collet-Serra's storyboard decisions feel the same and even the colour grading seems to gloom across all this transportation method trilogy. However, although it's completely uneventful, I didn't dislike The Commuter. There's a security in a commute like this where the elements are so played out that they are bound to work. Furthermore, there is one shot that is incredibly good and there is actual tension built around a premise, which many action films fail to do. It's like going to work in an office, it's a service and in this case, enough has been done to make it serviceable. It's incoherent but it has a lot of personal style, it's cookie-cutter but it is sufficiently well put together to make you actually care and feel some suspense for what's going to happen next. It's no Unstoppable or (for Hitchcock's sake) Strangers on a Train, but its main strength comes from the realization that the movie consists on seemingly one-trick pony of a star kicking ass in yet another mode of transport. #thecommuter #liamneeson #verafarmiga #filmreview #filmcritic

Here's a list of all the new releases that I watched this month with my ratings. 1) Three billboards outside ebbing, Missouri - 9/10 I heard a lot of great things about this but I wasn't expecting to love it as much as I did. This was the first film I watched in 2018, and I expect it to be in my top 5 come the end of the year. Frances Mcdormand and Sam Rockwell were brilliant and I expect them both to win Oscars. ----------------------------- 2) Molly's game - 8/10 I didn't know anything about Molly Bloom going into this, and I think that made me enjoy the movie more because I didn't know how things ended up for her. Jessica Chastain was brilliant and really owned the movie - there isn't anyone who would have been better cast. ----------------------------- 3)Coco - 8/10 It's definitely up there with being one of the better Disney films. I didn't know a lot about the Day of the Dead but having seen this I feel like it's given me a whole new outlook on death - I thought the movie did a great job showing off the culture and tradition. ----------------------------- 4)The Commuter - 7/10 Liam Neeson on public transport fighting to keep his family alive. You knew exactly what you're going to get and it didn't disappoint. ----------------------------- 5) The Post - 7/10 I thought it was well made and had great performances from Meryl Streep and Tom Hanks. However I found the actual story to be quite boring in parts ----------------------------- 6) 12 Strong - 7/10 Although the actual true story is unbelievable, I thought the film fell short of capturing this. However I thought the action scenes were great and it had some good performances, showing that they were just normal men that were sent to fight. ----------------------------- 7) Hostiles 6/10 Again another one with decent performances, and when there was action it was quite intense. However when there wasn't any action it felt quite dull and dragged on a bit longer than it needed to be ----------------------------- 8) Early Man - 3/10 I knew this would be shit and it didn't fail at that, was full of stupid accents that were there to make little kids laugh. I'm not even sure if I like football anymore

"Altro giro, altra giostra!" Per dare più scelta al nostro pubblico cambiamo cercando sempre di diversificare la nostra offerta. Solo giovedì la nostra rassegna culturale con l'ennesima gemma di Haneke; cineasta geometrico, cinico, necessario. Nell'altra sala l'adrenalinico thriller con lo specialista Liam Neeson; una donna misteriosa, un treno affollato, una corsa contro il tempo. Da venerdì recuperiamo l'ultima opera americana di Virzì con due protagonisti d'oltreoceano che da soli meritano il biglietto; un on the road atipico che solo il regista toscano poteva filmare. Domenica pomeriggio ancora un appuntamento con un papà particolare ed un figlio che lo scopre straordinario nella sua diversità; un'animazione europea capace di toccare un tema delicato con leggerezza e svago. Infine vi ricordiamo da giovedì a domenica in orari apertura cassa cinema la prevendita di "50 sfumature di rosso". The show must go on! The Commuter (2018) - 6.7/10 61 “What kind of a person are you?” “Insurance salesman Michael is on his daily commute home, which quickly becomes anything but routine. After being contacted by a mysterious stranger, Michael is forced to uncover the identity of a hidden passenger on the train before the last stop. As he works against the clock to solve the puzzle, he realizes a deadly plan is unfolding, and he is unwittingly caught up in a criminal conspiracy that carries life and death stakes for everyone on the train.” At the beginning it was really confusing and slow, then it started getting better and better, developing the character more and setting more challenges. The storyline felt sometimes weird and without an actual point. The action scenes were good but everything seemed unnecessary, or overly exaggerated. The plot was a little confusing but the actors did a good job portraying their characters. It is overall an ok crime movie with some plot holes and the final rating is a 6.7/10, recommended. 61 9591Comment your opinion below9591 61 #movie #film #cinema #review #thecommuter #critique #fmcr #trains #crime #mystery

"The Commuter" was another thriller by Liam Neeson and it does not disappoint in the cinema, but when you're done with the movie, you kind of reflect back on the things that didn't make sense but did while you were watching it. First: thing: The Plot. I was very intrigued with the storyline but it did turn out a little bit unrealistic at the end. The mystery to the movie was acceptable but some parts were predictable and the person who did not belong on the train was not expected. Second: the cast and characters. Liam Neeson was pretty good in his role and Vera Farmiga was ok, so was Patrick Wilson. I did like how Jonathan Banks was in it because he was amazing in "Breaking Bad". Everyone else was average. Finally: the music and editing. The action scenes were not well done and the original score for the movie did not blend well with the whole suspense and plot. The editing is not really something to appreciate because (SPOILER) there is a scene where the train is moving sideways for a long amount of time and that is impossible. This movie wasn't a big success in reviews it it is a fan favorite now which is why I am going to rate this movie with a 62%. Thank you guys for reading my review and I'll see you next time. MOVIE REVIEW: If you're willing to turn your brain off and enjoy yourself, #TheCommuter is a surprisingly good time. There is a lot more tension and excitement than we anticipated. Much of the action enters into over the top, "what the hell is physics?" territory, but let's face it, we don't seek out #LiamNeeson action films for their realism. The mystery has a little bit of intrigue, though it is not tightly put together and we never felt wowed by that aspect of it. The camerawork gets pretty shaky at times and the jump-cuts come a bit too often, especially in the beginning when. #VeraFarmiga, #PatrickWilson, #FlorencePugh, #JonathanVanks, #ElizabethMcGovern, and #SamNeill don't get anything to do, but Neeson still keeps the entire thing rolling with help from director #JaumeColletSerra. You know it's going to contain some raw one on one violence, he'll be a cop or most likely an ex cop and he has to save some hostage/s from a certain situation.............. ..... 7373739804 He commutes to the big city and just lost his job and gets given a choice on the journey back that becomes the plot for the film 'Would you take $100k to help kill someone you have no connection with?' Well if you are Liam Neeson the answer is no. It's gritty, raw and really does leave you to the end before you grasp the whole plot which keeps it watchable. It's a churn out action film but if you are a fan then it's worth a watch but it's not going to win any awards. L’UOMO SUL TRENO 94 Chicken! Io non ci riesco a dare il Broccolo all’amico Liam Naason. A parte che ho paura che poi mi squilla il telefono ed è lui che mi fa “CB io ti troverò. E ti apparecchierò in testa per mangiarci antipasto, primo, secondo, contorno, dolce, caffè, ammazzacaffè e amaro.” E poi perché a dire la verità mi divertono sinceramente i suoi gero-action, che ve devo di’. Questa volta Liam se la deve vedere con dei misteriosi individui che gli offrono 100.000 soldi per trovare una persona nel treno di pendolari che lui prende (ma allora sono prendolari04). Lui accetta l’offerta ma quando tenta di tirarsi indietro scopre che questi erano dei farabutti... c’avrai pure un bel naso ma in quanto a fiuto per i guai Liam stai messo maluccio eh. Per fortuna non c’è nulla che un marcantonio di 2 metri con le mani larghe come vanghe non possa risolvere con due pizzoni. C’è meno action del solito, anche per l’ambiente un po’ ristretto dei vagoni, anche se non manca il combattimento in piano sequenza sborone. Mi raccomando salite sul treno lasciando a casa la ricerca di credibilità, altrimenti andate a fare trainspotting a Cinisello Balsamo e non rompete quando la gente vola da un vagone all’altro in corsa prendendo esattamente la porticina mentre io di solito quando devo andare alla carrozza ristorante mi cago sottissimo quando passi in mezzo tra uno e l’altro che trema tutto. Vale sempre la regola: se salite su un aereo, su un autobus, su una nave o su un treno e ci trovate #liamneeson ... Petit voyage dans un train de la Banlieue New Yorkaise avec The Passenger. Pour ce Thriller-Action, le réalisateur espagnol Jaume Collet-Serra va retrouver son acteur phare Liam Neeson. Et le moins que l’on puisse dire c’est que cette fois l’alchimie ne fonctionnera pas. On part sur une histoire assez basique. Un homme qui vient de se faire licencier rentre chez lui part un train de banlieue. Une femme s’assoie à c00té de lui et lui propose de l’argent en échange d’un petit service. Un choix qui fera basculer la vie de Michael MacCauley. Le casting a beau être intéressant, notamment avec le duo de Conjuring (Vera Farmiga & Patrick Wilson), cela ne compense pas un scénario beaucoup trop prévisible. J’aurai aimé plus de retournement de situation dans une trame qui se devine assez rapidement. De plus, un événement survenant vers la fin vous fera logiquement penser : 00 Mais en réalité tout ce qui vient de s’écouler été inutile 03. Certes, il y a une belle tentative pour compenser 04a par un rythme assez soutenu. Et je dois le reconnaitre je ne me suis pas du tout ennuyé durant le film. Mais malheureusement … les scènes d’action sont vraiment improbable. C’est donc avec un sentiment plut00t négatif que je suis sorti de la salle. Ich hatte Phasenweise Angst vor und Mitleid mit ihm. Es ist mal wieder genau die Rolle, die er spielen muss. Die Story selbst ist deutlich spannender als erwartet, hat einige Wendungen, ist super inszeniert und spannend. Man kann die ganze Zeit mitr01tseln. Erst wen er sucht, dann wer der b02se ist. Au08er man ist mit meiner Freundin im Kino - die wusste nach etwa 10 Minuten (nach dem im Trailer angeschnittenen Angebot) bescheid. Und sie behielt recht. Wie immer. Allerdings war das auch mein erster Gedanken. Den Film kann man sich auf jeden Fall im Kino ansehen, ich war durchgehend gut unterhalten (obwohl die ersten 20 Minuten nur Charakteraufbau war) und die Inszenierung schreit nach riesiger Leinwand und Popcorn.95 Viel spa08 7215 Und wenn ihr den Film gesehen habt, schreibt mir eure Meinung dazu. The Commuter (2018) Movie Review #thecommuter #moviereview #jimbobtalksmovies. SPOILERS (You have been warned). This is the first movie of 2018 I'm reviewing, The Commuter is a mixture of Non-Stop, Taken and Speed all in one if you ask me, is that a bad thing? No it's not but it is something we've all seen before. The Commuter stars Liam Neeson as Michael, an ex cop, husband and father who commutes on a train every day for work until one day he loses his job. On the train he is confronted by a strange woman who asks him to find a person on the train who does not belong and in return he gets $100,000. This movie is a race against the clock as Neeson puts all his best efforts and skills he learnt as a cop to try and find the mysterious character known as Prin who is aboard the train before his family is killed. The Commuter has great action sequences, it has 2 very good fight scenes that don't rely on great stunt work but make it work. Neeson once again is brilliant as the action hero but there are a few plot holes in this movie and it's nothing we haven't seen before, The Commuter is very much like Non-Stop but on a train. I'm glad they kept the character the same age as Neeson himself, he shows at 60 you can still throw quite a few punches and he always has that commanding presence which adds to the tone of his likeable characters. I personally found the 2nd half better than the first. It felt quite comparable to the film Speed (not as good) towards the end. Especially with the intensity of the music and slightly comparable situation. Overall its alot of fun, you go to see these sort of films for the entertaining action and the thrill of the main characters journey and challenges. I was looking forward to this film as I've always enjoyed films with trains, I don't know why but I always find that setting intense and thrilling and enjoyable to watch. I look forward to the iTunes HD release! I look forward to more of these films!! The Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Final Part The direction by Jaume Collet-Serra is grounded as well it can be on a train-location and is appropriately silly when it needs to be when the film shows its flair for action. I did like the opening montage however, that shows the day-to-day life of It's a film that's fully aware of what a Liam Neeson action film is, overdoses a little bit with the concept, gives Neeson plenty of arse to kick and he kicks it bloody well in one one-take fight sequence. So I suppose this film might deserve a 2/5 rating, right? Well it goes back to point I made at the start of this: there's a time and a place for a Liam Neeson action flick. It's self-aware, has an interesting if flawed concept that falls flat eventually and knows what it wants to do as a straight-up action film. The kind of mindless action film that used to get produced and released a lot in the 80's and 90's. It's the kind of film that you might think would be worth it on home-release, but in all honesty, if you don't take the film too seriously, it might just be worth the 055 film ticket - but perhaps not more. It does it's job in being a very flawed entertaining Liam Neeson action vehicle. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

The Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Part 3 The cast do a lot with very little, or at least a very thin script and for the most part they're all capable. It just seems that some of the actors are capable of much more and deserve more when it comes to a better and competent script, rather than just being functional entities to the plot. The plot itself seems to forget the setup half-way through and the film then returns to familiar ground: Liam Neeson beating the shit out of bad guys, or rather other commuters. I dunno, maybe it's something we can sympathise with and want to do when on our commutes with fellow commuters of the annoying variety. I did hate the sort of "Unstoppable" moment that the film took with the train concept towards the end of the film and it was just pointless and a drastic shift in the film's already troubled pacing. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

The Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Part 2 Admittedly, I haven't actually seen Taken in full, nor have I seen any of the action movies that he has starred in recent years; I've just never really had a chance to get into them and watch them properly for some reason. I think it's important to remember that there's a special place reserved in cinemas for the straight-forward, hard and tough-as-nails action/crime/thriller genre movies akin to those of 70s Hollywood films. The sort of films that you could just sit back, watch, take it in and just enjoy. Neeson has managed to do something really special over the last decades with his career in this respect, being involved in the sort of films that you can watch and be entertained by very easily. The beauty of The Commuter is in it's Hitchcock-like simplicity in terms of the plot (at first). This gradually deteriorates however and less favourable when it overdoses on the action part way through. An ex-cop turned normal insurance salesman (those cop "skills" will come in handy no doubt...wink-wink) on a train, put in the right place at the right time, by the wrong people for the wrong reasons, forced to do some bad things. A labyrinthine game of Saw-like proportions begins; it's a race against time, a race against Neeson's own paranoia, where everyone on board the train is his target. It's the simple and one-location game that takes place and the films thriller moments that makes this entertaining. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

The Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Part 1 There's a time and place for a Liam Neeson action flick. Sometimes something is taken. I've often heard Neeson has a particular set of skills, skills that make him a nightmare for the bad bastards who get in his way; and if he doesn't get what he wants, he looks for said bad bastards, find them, beats them up and kills them. Maybe he does this in different countries, maybe he does this whilst taking a taxi or plane trip or against wolves in the wild. Essentially, we know Liam Neeson beating the shit out of bad guys, on the big-screen is worth a watch, even if the story heavily falters. So with that in mind, how does The Commuter fair? Pretty well if you're looking if you're not looking for much in consistency and just want to sit back for a silly watch. Since Neeson's career took a major turning point in 2008 with the release of Taken, he redefined his career and has been in the action film business since and shows no signs of stopping any time soon. As well as being a formidable actor with tremendous gravitas (see Schindler's List, Gangs of New York, Batman Begins, Kingdom of Heaven) he lends himself to the action movie genre very well, delivering capable performances whilst delivering on the action-front from a physical perspective, putting effort into the fighting and action sequences. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

#TheCommuter was my first official movie of 2018 ... and shit ... it couldn't start worse. I like Collet-Serra and his movies. I like Neeson and his action roles. This was to me unnecessary filled with action. It was to the point of stupidity and absurdity. I liked the set up for the movie, but after first stop (second?) when certain character dies, it just goes to hell and never came back. What could have been suspensful movie, (which Collet-Serra can do), was just washed out, boring and annoying movie. Action sequences were good, I'll give them that, but they didn't fit it. Movie tried to be smart, I'll give them that, but it didn't work. It was predictable, uneventful, also long, with bad characters I didn't care about for a split second. Avoid this movie in cinemas, rent it if you so desire later this year. 1/5* P.S. First movie since #WonderWoman when I stormed out of cinema right when credits were about to roll ... and the final scene ... oh lord ... I could rant for so long ... aaaaaaah. P.S.S. At the opening credits there was really funny bit - to me at least - Sam Neil's named showed up, and I went "Whaaaat ..." split second later Neeson's character said "What" in the movie. I thought it was maybe directors decission to acknowladge fact Sam Neill is in this movie and it might surprise some people me included - I'm probably reading to much into it. #Movies

The Commuter- 7/10 61A common businessman is caught in the middle of a conspiracy on the way home61 The Commuter impressed me in a lot of ways I didn’t expect it to. For an action movie I found it surprising that most scenes were dialogue driven and the film was very heavy on plot. While it’s always exciting to watch people beat the crap out of each other for two hours straight, I found this gave the film lots of depth, allowing the full investment and attention of the audience, and causing an action scene (when it does occur) to have all the more impact and intensity. Another thing that is always important is that cause is given to the main character and in the Commuter I feel like relationships were very established. If they weren’t you wouldn’t care who died or why, or even about the main character at all. On top of that, the logic for this movie was rock solid. If I was ever questioning the reasoning of the main character, the problem would immediately be explained or resolved. My problem with this movie is unfortunately a big one. While the hand to hand fight scenes were fantastic to watch, often taking you right into them, the de-railing of the train was extremely dragged out and felt absolutely unnecessary. La quatrième collaboration entre Liam Neeson et Jaume Collet-Sera se déroule cette fois-ci à bord d'un train. C'est un quasi huis clos plut00t efficace même si 04a manque de tension. On ne sent pas vraiment de menace et on a du mal à se mettre à la place du personnage. Le scénario est plut00t bon même si 04a manque de rebondissements. Par contre, les effets spéciaux sont pour la majorité plut00t loupés et on a l'impression qu'ils ont quelques années de retard. Liam Neeson fait du Liam Neeson des années 2010 et commence, à l'instar de son personnage, à fatiguer un peu. Bref, c'est assurément un très bon film de dimanche soir sur TF1. Est Ce que 04a vaut de se déplacer? What’s better than a 65 year old Liam Neeson STILL kicking ass, in an action packed thriller? Nothing! #TheCommuter is a fast paced, adrenaline rush type of movie that will have you sweating and leaning over your seat. With the likes of Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson and Jonathan Banks, starring alongside - this is definitely not one you want to miss. The mysterious storyline, combined with the train setting will have you scratching at your head, thinking: WHO IS THIS PERSON? And what do they want from Michael, an insurance salesman? It’s safe to say that my daily commute to work will never feel the same again. I’d be better off walking to work. Catch The Commuter out in cinemas now - and ask yourself, when faced with a situation that will affect someone else’s life; what would you do? What kind of person are you? Taaaim to review!!! Ok, sedikit telat nonton film ini dan sedikit keganggu sama temennnya temen yg sebelum teathre buka bilang, "filmnya ga seberapa bagus". Well, dari menit menit pertama saya udah bisa menilai kalo temannya teman saya tadi brengsek. Come on! Ini tipical film suspense klasik!! Dan kayaknya bukan saya saja yang rindu film yang bikin kita ikutan deg degan dalam kereta yg terus berlari. Film ini ngingetin kita gimana rasanya tiap hari pakai public transport dan bagaimana bagaimana lainnya kalo ketemu orang yg nyaris sama tiap harinya. Dan tanpa diduga duga, kamu kejebak dalam kengerian psikologis "the Conjuring Universe" versi live action. Yes! Menyuntikkan Formula ini lumayan ampuh menyeret penonton ikut dalam Ketegangan-Kepepet-Keburu seorang bapak sekaligus mantan polisi yg masih memiliki rasa patriotis. Overall OK, hanya saja ancaman utama pada tokoh utama terasa kurang greget dan tempo yg sedikit melemah karena terlalu banyak pertimbangan di tengah film. Menegangkan, tapi masih membuatmu bisa bernafas. Dan saya jamin tidak akan membuatmu menyumpahi film ini saat keluar teathre. #RulliReview #MovieReview #Movie #Review #TheCommuter #Malang #LiamNeeson

"THE COMMUTER." (Still Showing on Bioskop 909898) . Cerita yang ditawarkan The Commuter relatif sederhana, hampir sama dengan film-film Liam Neeson sebelumnya seperti Taken dan Non-Stop ― Liam Neeson diminta menyelesaikan sebuah tugas demi menyelamatkan keluarganya. . Meskipun premis cerita yang ditawarkan cenderung membosankan, tapi tidak membuat film ini kehilangan keistimewaannya. Penonton dibuat seolah-olah ikut berada di dalam kereta, merasakan ancaman yang ada. Apa lagi bagi para anker (anak kereta) yang sehari-harinya menggunakan kereta commuter line untuk beraktivitas. . Adegan action di dalam kereta juga cukup membuat jantung terpacu saat menonton film ini. Twist dibagian akhir yang cukup tak tertebak juga membuat film ini sangat patut untuk disaksikan, terutama bagi para penggemar film Liam Neeson sebelumnya. Perasaan kaget, tegang, dan naiknya adrenalin pasti akan dirasakan saat menonton film berdurasi 105 menit ini. . . Siapa yang belum nonton? Yakin ga penasaran sama film yang satu ini? El Pasajero (Jaume Collet-Serra) y Parte 4 Lo más importante, como en todas las cintas de este tipo, es dejarse llevar por la convención. Jugar el juego de ir descifrando, dejando de ver lo obvio a veces y disfrutar sin preguntas la acción y la intriga, el fervoroso homenaje que a su modo realiza Collet-Serra a las obras de Hitchcok y la presencia de Liam, que una vez más salva el día, digamos que en contra de todo presagio… o no? El Pasajero (Jaume Collet-Serra) Parte 3 Collet-Serra y sus escritores mantienen la tensión por las dos primeras partes de la trama de forma muy efectiva porque el verdadero lado salvaje de Liam (aunque lo esperemos) no se destapa sino hasta entrando al último tercio de la película. Vera Farmiga merece una mención, porque con solo unos minutos en pantalla se apodera de la esencia del mal en el sentido de la película. Todo lo que hace después es usar un tono de voz por teléfono que se regocija en el “cacle cacle” de bruja definitiva y modernamente perversa. El Pasajero (Jaume Collet-Serra) Parte 2 El desenlace del argumento es predecible, aunque logra puntos de intriga bastante efectivos. Neeson una vez más es golpeado, zarandeado y debe hacer acrobacias mientras deduce que es lo que sigue. Pero eso no es raro, El Pasajero es una típica cinta de esas sin presencia de elementos de ciencia ficción, dedicada a la acción y diversión para hombres y eso es lo esperado. Aunque algunas cosas se desmoronan… no importa demasiado mientras siga la acción a tope. “Lives Are On The Line.” 7415DIRECTED BY: Jaume Collet-Serra STARRING: Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, and Patrick Wilson PLOT SUMMARY: Insurance salesman Michael MacCauley is on his daily commute home, which quickly becomes anything but routine. After being contacted by a mysterious stranger, Michael is forced to uncover the identity of a hidden passenger on the train before the last stop. As he works against the clock to solve the puzzle, he realizes a deadly plan is unfolding, and he is unwittingly caught up in a criminal conspiracy that carries life and death stakes for everyone on the train. PROS: -Liam Neeson (successfully plays “his” role...struggling family man in trouble) Interesting Concept (makes viewers think what they would do in the situation) CONS: -Predictable Plot -Lack of Tension/Intensity -Leaves Unanswered Questions BOTTOM LINE: The Commuter is next movie of the director/actor team-up between Jaume Collet-Serra and Liam Neeson. These two are respon for sible similar action movies in the past together such as, Unknown, Non-Stop, and Run All Night. I went into this movie hoping to receive a film similar to Non-Stop, due to myself personally enjoying that film a lot, but instead, I got a dulled down version with this movie. Since seeing previous films from this director, I knew exactly where the story was going to go. I turned to my friend, who I saw this with, and told him who was behind the whole hostage plot within the first five minutes of the movie. I can’t really recommend this movie because I found myself falling asleep during parts of the movie, that were intended to be intense. Joanna: Let’s do an experiment. What if I asked you to do something that could profoundly affect an individual on this train? Michael McCauley: I don’t understand. Joanna: It’s just one little thing. Someone on this train does not belong, all you have to do is find them. Liam Neeson stars as Michael MacCauley a businessman who is caught up in a criminal conspiracy during his daily commute home. If you think this is just another Liam Neeson movie with Liam Neeson being Liam Neeson and doing Liam Neeson type things...you would be correct! Let’s be honest at this point your not going to see a movie starring Liam Neeson and expect an intricate storyline or world class cinematography. But what you can always expect is a fun ride. The Commuter delivers on that promise with just that, plenty of action and a few good twist every now and then. Pros: Hitchcock: What makes this film fun is that it really seems to draw on an Alfred Hitchcock vibe of whodunnit? Vera Farmiga: best known for her roles as Norma Bates in Bates Motel & The Departed. Farmiga always delivers a convincingly good role. In this case, as a great antagonist Cons: I mean to really pick at this film -Expected corny Lines -While some of the twist were good. A few were so typical you could see a mile away Overall Rating 7/10 #movies #liamneeson #thecommuter #film #cinemark

The Commuter. Seen this twice now, both in IMAX! Films like these rarely get made anymore, but when they do they sure do pack a lot of suspense, thrills and old school action that really make for a captivating fun ride! Directed by Juame Collet-Serra and starring Liam Neeson The Commuter marks their fourth collaboration together (Uknown, Non-Stop, Run All Night and now this) and the two deliver yet another thrilling, edge of your seat action film that does well in mixing mystery and action into one! Serra is one of the best directors in the industry, and does not get the credit he deserves! Neeson, once again, kicks serous ass and proves why he is one of the best action hero's of our time! This film was entertaining and had only a small budget of 30 million dollars, which is quite low compared to a majority of action films made these days! Serra and Neeson should definitely reteam for a fifth film together! And next up for Neeson, Hard Powder, which will be more Neeson killing bad guys and being badass! #TheCommuter #Film #Action #Thriller #JuameColletSerra #LiamNeeson #Badass #Filmmaking #Director #Actor

My Rating: 55/100 The Commuter is the newest action film in the line-up of action movies starring Liam Neeson. This movie had some really cool actions sequences that were very well directed, but the overall film lacked in emotional depth and character development. The Commuter is just a fun action movie that is not really meant to blow audiences away. I didn’t really like this movie, and that’s because of the extremely predictable plot twists and very cringe-worthy performances. The Commuter is fun, but that’s it. The two main redeeming qualities to this movie are the action-set pieces and the storyline. I would highly recommend this movie to fans of mindless-action, but if not a fan of cheesy and predictable action movies, don’t bother. #thecommuter THE COMMUTER Information: Release Year: 2018 Runtime: 1 hr 45 min Content Rating: PG-13 (US) 61 14A (CAN) My Age Recommendation: 15+ Genres: Action, Mystery, Thriller Budget: $30,000,000 Director: Jaume Collet-Serra

Well this is a simple review that will be nice and short *ahem* if you have seen Non-Stop, Speed or Taken you've seen this film and I would urge you not to waste your time on this extremely average action-thriller. As this film has the same director and star as Non-Stop it just felt lazy as it followed all the same beats and didn't bring anything fresh or new except instead of being on a plane he's on a train and that was really disappointing. How do they expect me to believe a 60 year old man can win every fight he's in with guys half his age and then when done go and question a stranger on why they're on the train!!?? This film had so many horrible plot holes that it had me constantly rolling my eyes and by the hour mark I was begging for it to end! "The Commuter" Director : Jaume Collet-Serra Cast : Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson, Jonathan Banks,... Pelem yang berkesan bagi pengguna commuter, tapi commuter nya beda dengan di Indonesia walaupun sama2 penuh dan ramai.. Nonton "The Commuter" ini lengkap dapat action dan dramanya. Dan suaranya om Liam yang Optimus Prime nya transformer itu nambah keseruan dari film ini.. Diawali dengan adegan keluarga di Amerika, suami istri bekerja untuk melunasi hutang. Walaupun sudah bekerja sampai usia 60thn tetap saja dipecat. Michael (Liam Neeson) yg mantan polisi, dipecat dari perusahaan asuransi tempat ia bekerja selama 10thn, kemudian masuk perangkap seorang wanita bernama Joana (Vera Farmiga), sosok misterius yg muncul di commuter yg biasa ditumpanginya.. Alur cerita cukup seru, ga ketebak dan menegangkan... The Commuter Time to kick my 2018 movies off with a Liam Neeson action movie. I’ll be honest with you, this movie doesn’t look good. It looks like another cheesy action flick, but Liam Neeson is the reason I’m seeing this movie. The guy has had his fair share of bad movies, but this is from the same guy who did Non-Stop. Non-Stop looked like a cheesy action movie, but it actually turned out to be good, I enjoyed most of it. I’m willing to give this movie a chance. I do find some cheesy action movies more enjoyable then the average movie goer cause I like action. Action movies are an easy to do but hard to pull off form of entertainment. I’m not expecting much from this movie, I’m just expecting to be entertained. So with that in mind let’s see what we have in store for us. A businessman is caught up in a criminal conspiracy during his daily commute home. I definitely got what the director was trying to do here, I just think he tried to do too much. This movie starts off simple enough, then once the main plot starts things get really out of hand. I was asking more questions then this movie was answering. Pretty much this movie sets up a bunch of rules for the main character to follow, if he doesn’t follow these rules his family dies, but the main character breaks a bunch of these rules in the second act and nothing happens. There were so many plot holes with this movie that I lost enjoyment by the third act. Also the more this movie goes on, the more insane this movie gets. I was able to find some enjoyment in the middle when the mystery aspect was still in play. So I can give this movie some credit for the second act, but that’s not much considering how confusing this movie can be. The Commuter tries to recapture the mystery aspect of Non-Stop, but the more information this movie adds to the plot the more confusing it is. Much like any other Liam Neeson action movie, he carries the whole movie. He plays Michael MacCauley who’s an ex cop who is taking the train home one day and he must find a suspect a woman is looking for or else people die. It’s easy to have sympathy for this character and he is likable and noble. Continued in Comments.

THE COMMUTER C 2018 STARS: 6/10 While I think it is fair to say that this is a film in which the action sequences and CGI actually serve the storyline rather than rule it, too much prevenance is still given to eye-candy visuals, resulting in an undeniably entertaining but both implausible and overdone ride on something as basic as a commuter train. The piece is exceptionally well edited and filmed though C or perhaps creatively is the more appropriate word, for the visuals are neither sweeping nor seamless, merely intriguing. Indeed the entire piece reeks of that same intrigue; that fascinating yet decidedly staged vibe that grabs you and draws you in, despite everything your heart and mind tells you. Yes, perhaps you can never be fully engrossed in a story that is so obviously fabricated, but you can certainly be entertained C and that is this film's main plus as far as I am concerned; the ability to hold an audience on an unemotionally connected level. Not unlike one of those cheap but addictive cops and robbers style shows one might see in the evening on television, "The Commuter" somehow manages C with, literally, a hundred suspects, a hundred questions and a virtual time bomb ticking away throughout C to be drawn out, predictable and ultimately unimpressive . . . yet still watchable; still something you would sit down to and not move on from. There is some part of all of us C perhaps C that relishes hours upon hours of unabashed improbability and even as you pretend disinterest in this piece I warrant you will find yourself coming back to that one fateful catch question: what would you do?

Written by Carlos Crestwell Movie #3 The Commuter. At this point what can you say. Liam Neeson has never been short on work but sense Taken released in 2008 he has been in a steady stream of these well written suspense protagonist vs X dangerous antagonist. He does them very well and as much as you’d like to say enough. Neeson is always so compelling to to sit down and watch that you can’t help but check out his films. This role is no different as he pairs up again with director Jaume Collet-Serra who he’s been around the block with a few times (Non-Stop, Run All Night, Unknown). In this role he plays former NYPD detective turned insurance salesmen Michael MacCauley. A family man with a repetitively boring existence working a 9-5 to support his family. He gets put into a dangerous situation by a mysterious stranger on his usual train route home and Liam Neeson starts to do his thing. Co-stars Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson help make up the small bit of star power in this film but it’s well executed seeing how most these films never lose sight of Neeson as their focus. Still another well executed suspense film with very few complaints. These films rarely get too deep in the weeds which is probably a good thing. #Thecommuter #Copperwiire #Loscinema2018

The Commuter For god sake Liam, keep your family with you at all times! Now the story of this film is a little bazaar, but it keeps you gripped even if it is set on one of the worst forms of public transport. The film follows Michael MacCauley (Liam Neeson) on his daily commute to his job as an insurance salesman. He has had this job for 10 years and sadly gets let go. On his train ride home that day, a women named Joanna joins Michael in the seat opposite. She posses a hypothetical question where he has to do one thing and in return can earn $100,000. This hypothetical turns out to be real when Michael must find a passenger on the train who doesn't belong who goes by the allias of "Prynne" before Cold springs station or there will be consequences. He just has to find "Prynne" to get the $100,000, but as time runs out and his family become endangered, Michael must figure out who he can and can't trust. Check the Trailer here Now being a big Liam Neeson fan i enjoyed this film. To me all his films are the same, the plot is changed up a bit but most of the films feel formulaic and i found myself thinking alot about Taken. This film although different has alot of action and Neesons character has the lives his family at stake again. For God sake Liam, keep your family with you at all time! That being sad although the movie feels similar to his others, it is still enjoyable and keeps you engaged as you try to work out who "Prynne" is . No spoilers but I totally knew who "Prynne" was. The movie is decent enough, plus Liam Neeson running through the train causing havoc, who doesn't wanna see that. An entertaining (and in some places very good) thriller movie. Basic overview without spoiling, is that on his commute back from work Liam Neeson's character is approached by a mysterious woman (Vera Farmiga) who offers him $100,000 to find someone on the train who doesn't belong there and it escalates from there. All the cast are great Neeson is as good as the character type as usual, Patrick Wilson & Vera Farmiga are good supports. Also one thing I didn't expect was too actually find the train passengers as interesting, likeable and well written as they were. The film has some excellent writing and tense directing most so in the dialogue and scenes where he's starting awkward conversations to try and work out who's who and when he's is pacing up and down train trying to work out the situation. The film excels in these areas as they are more thrilling than the action sequences, one of which is awesome (Neeson fighting a dude with a guitar) and delivering an epic one liner after, however the other main fight sequences are just average and you've seen them loads of times before. Speaking of seen before this film doesn't bring much new to the table, if you've seen 'Non-Stop' or other Neeson movies you've basically watched this (not that's that's a bad thing). The ending is fairly predictable and the third act slows down a bit and makes the pacing a bit off and there's some dodgy CGI in places. Overall this a entertaining movie that does what it sets out to do and it's worth a watch for sure 9199#thecommuter#2018#liamneeson#verafarmiga#patrickwilson#jaumecolletserra#movie#film#cinema

The Commuter (2018) Movie Maniac rating: 3.5/5 It's the fourth collaboration between Liam Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra, and it's also the 7th time Liam Neeson played a tough guy character ever since he starred in Taken. The Commuter feels like a combination of 2011's Source Code (for the train setting) and 2014's Non-Stop (for the mystery killer on board of a moving transportation, and Liam Neeson presence). But despite the average reviews by fellow critics, I really enjoy this movie and this movie is better than Unknown, Non-Stop, and Run All Night. I personally like the editing of the beginning of the movie, the fast forward scenes are unique. The story, well there is no such thing in real world, is unbelievable but it works right on this movie, the villain resembles the villain in 2008's Eagle Eye in which the villain has an eye and ear anywhere and can do anything that sounds impossible. Liam Neeson plays the character very well, mostly like his previous good family man and highly skilled tough guy character. The action scenes are good, some of it are thrilling in fact. The movie really entertains and keeps you guessing until the climax of the movie. Another thing to add, I personally like the drama side of this movie where Liam Nesson's character got laid off from work and he has a burden to finance his kid's tuition. It is realistic and depicts the harsh thing in our lives. In my opinion, if you like Liam Neeson and his previous action movies, then you must see this movie. Don't expect a realistic storyline, just enjoy the movie and have a good time. #thecommuter #liamneeson #movies #film #hollywood #review #hobby #action #2018 @thecommuterfilm @lionsgate @cinema.21 @cinemaxxtheater @cgv.id @cinemagsnews

The Commuter is a 2018 action thriller film directed by Jaume Collet-Serra. The film follows a man who is unwittingly recruited into a murder conspiracy after meeting a mysterious woman while on his daily train commute. Pros: I go in with zero knowledge of what this film is about and a very low expectation (since you know, it’s a January movie). To my surprise, this is a very solid and entertaining movie with a rather unique premise. It leans heavily towards the mystery-thriller aspect, which is a truly refreshing idea to make the movie stand out (at least for the first half of the runtime). It raises some interesting questions about the morality of the main character, and in a way also allows the character develop in a more entertaining fashion. Liam Neeson’s performance is fantastic and he has a very impressive fight scene around the second act of the film. Cons: I’d like to call the main issue with this film “the escalation problem”. The film does some very questionable and inconsistent decisions throughout the story just in order to escalate the stakes higher and higher every time. At some point it turns from an engaging crime thriller with detective works into an over-the-top full blown action film for no apparent reason other than trying to make the film seemingly have a bigger stakes. There are a lot of plotholes made during this process and honestly I’d rate this with a much higher score had it simply been a contained thriller inside a train. Verdict: The Commuter is a very pleasant surprise for January movies. It’s an engaging thriller film with interesting premise, although at some point the film tries to bite more than it can chew. The Commuter (2018) - film review The Commuter presents a compelling mystery that keeps me invested. The plot is interesting and the mystery unveils smoothly. The main character Michael played by Liam Neeson is a character that has a believable motivation for his actions in the film, which also helps his character to be one that is easy to root for. The action scenes are not bad, but nothing new or especially well done is presented. The opening sequence of the film is quite well made with interesting editing style. The CGI is poorly done but fortunately it isn’t relied too much by the film. Some scenes challenge the edge of possibility and this can be slightly annoying. Overall the film is not particularly inventive or brilliantly crafted, but it is undoubtedly a decent and somewhat enjoyable watch. 7/10 #thecommuter #film #movie #filmreview

MOVIE REVIEW: The Commuter [2018] Director: Jaume Collet-Serra Stars: Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson, Jonathan Banks, Ella-Rae Smith Colin McFarlane, Shazad Latif and Sam Neill Review: Who would’ve thought star Liam Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra would’ve done four collaborations together now. While Unknown, Non-Stop and Run All Night aren’t anything amazing, they’re still solid action movies, as is The Commuter. While the film is in many ways Non-Stop on a train, it’s still a fun, engaging thriller. Liam Neeson as always puts in 110%, even though he’s definitely getting “too old for this sh*t”. He’s so uncompromisingly likeable and just someone so easy to get behind. Vera Farmiga was disappointingly bland, but her part didn’t require much. Patrick Wilson delivered strong in a bigger role than I had expected. Sam Neill was also a surprise as I wasn’t expecting to see, but a pleasant one at that. All the other cast members on the train were also fantastic. Director Jaume Collet-Serra doesn’t make movies you think about for days after days, but he excels at just engaging you for 2 hours and making you walk out pleased. Collet-Serra also masters at contained thrillers, brilliantly using every location and making the most of them. The plot is also genuinely intriguing. Of course it’s filled with many cliche and predictable elements, but all in all it kept me invested. I don’t think The Commuter has as great rewatch value as let’s say Non-Stop or Run All Night, but that’s not a negative. Overall, as this’s my first 2018, I think the year is off to a pretty solid start, especially for January. Rating: B- Reviewer: @declanwilson_

After being contacted by a mysterious stranger, Michael is forced to uncover the identity of a hidden passenger on the train before the last stop. As he works against the clock to solve the puzzle, he realizes a deadly plan is unfolding & he is unwittingly caught up in a criminal conspiracy that carries life & death stakes for everyone on the train. I didn’t think much about it at first but after seeing the film it was very #Suspenseful which made it #Enjoyable, #LiamNeeson I understand that the character that he plays in some action films are the same which in this film it does seem like that in some areas especially when he has a gun in his hand but he really does an Amazing job with his acting in this, I really liked #VeraFarmiga’s character in this telling Liam’s character to find person on the train that does not belong which is actually quite genius, #PatrickWilson, #JonathanBanks, #AndyNyman, #ElizabethMcGovern, #SamNeill, #DeanCharlesChapman, #FlorencePugh, #ClaraLago & the rest of the cast was #Good too, The Suspenseful #Thriller genre for me was definitely the highlight of this film & the #Action goes along really well as well, I do have to be honest I have to agree with the fact that yes there are similarities of other Liam Neeson action films which again is understandable but it does get jarring but at least it didn’t halt me from enjoying the whole film, So inclosing really #Good film, #8outof10.
